WEBVTT

00:01.336 --> 00:04.233
♪ Crazy is when I go off the rails ♪

00:04.258 --> 00:07.292
♪ This is what you've done to me ♪

00:07.294 --> 00:10.028
♪ Crazy is how your
loving makes me feel ♪

00:10.030 --> 00:13.187
♪ This is what I always want to be ♪

00:13.212 --> 00:16.155
♪ I like it when a
girl gets crazy in bed ♪

00:16.181 --> 00:19.242
♪ Don't mess with the bitch
who's crazy in the head ♪

00:20.695 --> 00:22.101
- ♪ You do ♪
- ♪ You don't ♪

00:22.126 --> 00:23.592
♪ Want to be crazy ♪

00:23.617 --> 00:24.914
- ♪ And you don't ♪
- ♪ You do ♪

00:24.939 --> 00:26.238
♪ Want to be crazy ♪

00:26.263 --> 00:30.099
♪ To clarify, yes, no on the crazy ♪

00:30.420 --> 00:33.085
♪ We hope this helps. ♪

00:34.916 --> 00:35.859
What?

00:35.883 --> 00:37.375
-- Synced and corrected by ChrisKe --
-- www.addic7ed.com --

00:37.391 --> 00:39.157
Previously on Crazy Ex-Girlfriend...

00:39.159 --> 00:40.359
If I'm crazy,

00:40.361 --> 00:41.493
you made me crazier

00:41.495 --> 00:43.528
because your life is broken and boring.

00:43.530 --> 00:45.631
I'm sick and tired of you!
I want you out of my life!

00:45.633 --> 00:46.921
REBECCA: I've officially alienated

00:46.938 --> 00:48.271
every person I know.

00:48.273 --> 00:50.073
I give up.

00:50.075 --> 00:51.474
I'll come home.

00:51.476 --> 00:53.776
Darling, it's time that I take
over the reins of your life.

00:53.778 --> 00:55.078
You're incapable.

00:55.080 --> 00:57.046
You made me think that you loved me.

00:57.821 --> 01:00.016
You gave me hope
when I had none.

01:00.018 --> 01:01.954
And now, that hope is gone.

01:02.320 --> 01:05.048
- Is everything okay?
- I need help.

01:11.180 --> 01:13.180
_

01:16.334 --> 01:18.835
Oh, sorry.

01:20.205 --> 01:21.637
She's okay.

01:21.639 --> 01:23.005
She's out of the woods for now.

01:23.007 --> 01:24.702
- Oh...
- Oh, thank God.

01:24.727 --> 01:26.117
I knew she'd be fine.

01:26.142 --> 01:28.079
The minute I heard,
that's what I told myself.

01:28.104 --> 01:30.376
All right, I got to get back in there.

01:30.618 --> 01:32.413
Dr. Akopian is leaving,

01:32.415 --> 01:34.517
and Rebecca needs somebody in
the room with her at all times.

01:34.542 --> 01:36.946
Uh, they assigned a nurse to be
her “sitter” or something,

01:36.971 --> 01:38.993
but I got rid of her.
And so, now,

01:39.018 --> 01:43.446
all I have to do is fend off
a very overeager housekeeper

01:43.471 --> 01:45.235
who just keeps
interrupting for no reason.

01:45.260 --> 01:46.727
- VALENCIA: Paula.
- Yeah?

01:46.752 --> 01:48.188
You don't have to do this by yourself.

01:48.213 --> 01:49.978
We can help, we can take turns.

01:50.009 --> 01:51.409
Yeah, you have a family at home.

01:51.411 --> 01:52.710
Don't be silly. Rebecca needs me.

01:52.712 --> 01:54.431
And my family will understand.

01:55.595 --> 01:57.181
Actually, there is another
way you guys can help.

01:57.183 --> 01:59.884
So, she knows everyone is
hearing about what happened.

01:59.886 --> 02:01.538
I mean, her phone is blowing up...

02:01.563 --> 02:04.622
Lots of concerned people,
really sweet, very annoying.

02:04.624 --> 02:07.281
Could you please just let
everyone know that she's okay?

02:07.306 --> 02:08.993
I could do it. I'll get
in touch with everyone.

02:08.995 --> 02:09.960
I want to help.

02:09.961 --> 02:11.896
- Oh, great.
- Hey.

02:12.103 --> 02:15.332
- I got here as fast as I could.
- Why?

02:15.923 --> 02:19.170
- Is Rebecca okay?
- For now. Josh, you need to leave.

02:19.501 --> 02:22.306
I can't have Rebecca seeing you
or hearing you.

02:22.331 --> 02:24.314
I don't want her to be upset.

02:24.339 --> 02:26.372
In fact, I am worried

02:26.374 --> 02:28.408
that your body spray is
gonna waft into her room

02:28.410 --> 02:29.909
and she's gonna know that you're here,

02:29.934 --> 02:32.935
so leave... without wafting.

02:34.516 --> 02:35.548
(Paula sighs)

02:35.550 --> 02:37.917
Dude, you should go.

02:37.919 --> 02:39.452
But I want to talk to Rebecca.

02:39.454 --> 02:41.754
I mean, last time I saw her,
we had a really bad fight

02:41.756 --> 02:44.023
and I said I wanted her
to go away, which I did,

02:44.025 --> 02:46.626
but not in, like, a permanent way.

02:47.727 --> 02:49.160
Will you at least tell her I was here?

02:49.996 --> 02:51.957
- No...
- No.

02:52.575 --> 02:55.082
I'm so sorry, Dr. Akopian.

02:56.994 --> 02:58.193
I failed you.

02:59.661 --> 03:02.719
- God, I'm such a coward.
- You were no such thing.

03:02.744 --> 03:03.943
No such thing.

03:03.945 --> 03:06.312
You were brave. You asked for help.

03:06.314 --> 03:08.047
Brave. Asked for help.

03:08.533 --> 03:10.119
Just agreeing with you.

03:12.031 --> 03:14.532
I'll let you get some
rest, but don't worry,

03:14.557 --> 03:17.333
there are some great
psychiatrists on staff here,

03:17.553 --> 03:20.049
and we'll work together
to get you the right help.

03:24.778 --> 03:26.455
Thank you.

03:29.137 --> 03:30.984
- Hi.
- Hi.

03:31.531 --> 03:33.172
Are the girls still here?

03:33.174 --> 03:34.907
Oh, yeah. No, we're all here.

03:34.909 --> 03:37.643
# GirlGroup4Evah. (laughs)

03:37.929 --> 03:39.912
- Are they mad at me?
- No.

03:39.914 --> 03:42.248
- No one is mad.
- (door opens)

03:42.250 --> 03:44.172
Not now, Denise!

03:44.819 --> 03:47.353
Denise, what did I say?

03:47.355 --> 03:49.922
Sweetie, do you need anything?

03:49.924 --> 03:54.289
No, um, no, I think I'm
just gonna go to sleep.

03:54.629 --> 03:57.843
Oh. Oh, God.

03:58.347 --> 04:01.181
Oh, I'm so embarrassed
that I caused such a scene.

04:01.797 --> 04:04.851
And I didn't, I didn't even want to die.

04:05.502 --> 04:07.635
I just wanted the pain to stop.

04:07.942 --> 04:09.675
I know.

04:09.984 --> 04:12.612
(sniffles) It's like
I was out of stories

04:12.614 --> 04:14.614
to tell myself that
things would be okay.

04:15.523 --> 04:18.117
I just feel like I
inconvenienced a lot of people.

04:18.119 --> 04:20.890
No, no, no, no. No, you didn't.

04:21.422 --> 04:24.524
And don't you worry about
anyone else right now, okay?

04:24.526 --> 04:27.493
- (sniffles) Okay.
- Okay.

04:27.495 --> 04:29.762
♪ ♪

04:33.462 --> 04:35.596
(clears throat)

04:35.620 --> 04:37.604
_

04:37.605 --> 04:39.572
(typing)

04:39.574 --> 04:44.544
(reading words on screen): _

04:45.680 --> 04:47.413
Hmm.

04:47.437 --> 04:48.982
_

04:48.983 --> 04:50.383
(clears throat)

04:50.407 --> 04:52.407
_

04:59.490 --> 05:02.295
- Hey, boss. So, the whole office...
- (clears throat)

05:02.297 --> 05:04.396
... is going in on a
cupcake basket for Rebecca.

05:04.421 --> 05:06.254
Do you want to kick in some money or...

05:06.279 --> 05:07.427
probably doing your own thing?

05:07.452 --> 05:09.018
Yeah. No, I'm-I'm doing my own thing.

05:09.043 --> 05:10.747
Okay, so no money from you, then.

05:11.029 --> 05:13.239
Because I do need an extra eight bucks

05:13.241 --> 05:14.540
and I can't find Darryl.

05:14.542 --> 05:15.775
Called and texted him.

05:15.777 --> 05:18.411
He's at a yurt with his
boyfriend or something.

05:18.413 --> 05:19.865
Uh, he probably doesn't
have cell service.

05:20.248 --> 05:22.563
Are you okay?

05:22.588 --> 05:25.284
This must be tough, and
I know you care about her.

05:25.286 --> 05:28.421
- George, we're done here.
- For sure. Uh-huh.

05:31.092 --> 05:35.995
(sighs) All right, I
just have to do this.

05:35.997 --> 05:37.930
I'm gonna do it.

05:37.932 --> 05:38.931
(phone beeps)

05:38.933 --> 05:41.534
Hi, everyone, I'm Valencia Perez,

05:41.536 --> 05:42.768
Rebecca Bunch's friend.

05:42.770 --> 05:44.804
I wanted to just post a
quick update on Rebecca

05:44.806 --> 05:47.073
because I know a lot of
people are worried about her.

05:47.386 --> 05:51.077
Rebecca went through a tough
time a few days ago, obviously,

05:51.079 --> 05:52.278
but she's stable now

05:52.280 --> 05:54.280
and she appreciates
everyone thinking about her.

05:54.479 --> 05:56.515
If you want to connect with her,

05:56.517 --> 05:58.584
you can just write in the comments below

05:58.586 --> 06:00.486
and I will make sure
she gets the message.

06:00.488 --> 06:02.585
- Thanks, all.
- (phone beeps)

06:02.610 --> 06:04.824
You're posting a video?

06:04.826 --> 06:07.660
I thought you were gonna,
like, e-mail people.

06:07.662 --> 06:08.894
Seemed impersonal.

06:08.896 --> 06:10.596
I thought a Facebook
video would be better.

06:10.598 --> 06:12.431
I asked Paula, and she
said Rebecca thought

06:12.433 --> 06:13.566
it was a great idea.

06:13.568 --> 06:15.101
Okay, sounds good.

06:15.103 --> 06:18.304
Oh, where should I put these chips?

06:18.815 --> 06:21.340
Um, why is he here?

06:21.342 --> 06:24.810
Well, we were supposed
to go on our third date

06:24.812 --> 06:28.280
and I was gonna cancel, but then
he didn't want me to be alone.

06:28.282 --> 06:30.650
- (chuckles)
- That's sweet, right?

06:30.652 --> 06:32.151
Yeah, sure.

06:32.153 --> 06:34.654
I didn't know a friend's suicide
attempt was a plus one event,

06:34.656 --> 06:35.988
but cool.

06:35.990 --> 06:37.923
(quietly): I told you she might be mad.

06:37.925 --> 06:39.091
She gets like this.

06:39.093 --> 06:40.693
In third grade, she cut off my rat-tail

06:40.695 --> 06:42.094
'cause I sat in her desk once.

06:42.096 --> 06:45.364
Hector, just unpack the
cheese puffs... also, rat-tail?

06:45.536 --> 06:47.166
So many questions.

06:47.168 --> 06:48.801
Valencia, let's not be controlling.

06:48.803 --> 06:49.969
I don't think there are, like,

06:49.971 --> 06:52.138
rules for this kind of situation.

06:52.140 --> 06:53.650
(sighs) You're right.

06:53.809 --> 06:55.474
It's a tough time.

06:55.476 --> 06:56.997
We should be gentle with each other.

06:58.404 --> 07:01.138
- Bitch, don't get in my way, bitch.
- (yelps)

07:02.551 --> 07:04.817
Are you sure you don't
need to go be at home?

07:04.819 --> 07:06.752
What about your kids?

07:06.754 --> 07:09.522
And... the girls... I mean,
they haven't been to their jobs

07:09.524 --> 07:11.891
or anything in days; I just feel so bad.

07:11.893 --> 07:13.793
It's fine, it is fine.

07:13.795 --> 07:14.927
Paula,

07:14.929 --> 07:15.961
I'm okay here by myself.

07:15.963 --> 07:17.396
I mean, I got doctors and nurses,

07:17.398 --> 07:18.564
- and Denise.
- (door opens)

07:18.566 --> 07:21.649
Denise, I will strangle
you in your sleep!

07:23.102 --> 07:24.268
(door closes)

07:25.251 --> 07:26.672
Unbelievable.

07:26.674 --> 07:27.907
(sighs)

07:27.909 --> 07:31.343
Honey, do not worry about me.

07:31.345 --> 07:33.071
(sighs)

07:33.096 --> 07:36.949
I am where I should be,
which is right by your side.

07:36.951 --> 07:38.350
How's your throat feeling?

07:38.352 --> 07:41.454
Still a little scratchy from the
stomach pump and the barfing.

07:41.689 --> 07:44.690
Ugh, it was like all six
months of my college bulimia

07:44.692 --> 07:45.858
happened in one day.

07:45.860 --> 07:47.407
That was sassy.

07:47.595 --> 07:50.830
Sassy... my girl is still sassy.

07:50.832 --> 07:53.032
Mama, what's gonna happen
when I get out of here?

07:53.034 --> 07:54.924
Tell you what, let's not
worry about that right now.

07:55.937 --> 07:59.238
Because you are doing
everything you're supposed to.

07:59.263 --> 08:01.072
You met with a doctor,

08:01.097 --> 08:03.924
that... very nice-looking Dr. Shin,

08:03.949 --> 08:06.016
or, as I like to call him, Dr. Dan.

08:06.114 --> 08:09.263
Or, even better, Dr. Damn...

08:09.288 --> 08:12.083
- because he is so cute.
- Hmm.

08:12.108 --> 08:14.161
You were honest and brave.

08:14.186 --> 08:16.756
And they said that in a couple of days,

08:16.758 --> 08:18.005
you can go home.

08:18.030 --> 08:19.740
But that's what I'm nervous about.

08:20.546 --> 08:22.317
Once I go home...

08:23.118 --> 08:24.551
how will things be different?

08:24.732 --> 08:29.769
I... will not let you leave
here without a plan.

08:29.771 --> 08:31.704
Okay.

08:31.706 --> 08:34.774
♪ ♪

08:37.174 --> 08:40.496
VALENCIA: Hey, all. Thank you so
much for all your comments.

08:40.520 --> 08:43.482
Rebecca feels so encouraged and
she's making a lot of progress.

08:43.484 --> 08:45.317
I've read a lot of your comments to her

08:45.319 --> 08:46.552
and they really cheer her up.

08:46.809 --> 08:48.988
Now, get your liking fingers ready,

08:48.990 --> 08:52.491
because Rebecca is going home today.

08:52.493 --> 08:54.768
Yeah, she's talking to the
doctor, like, right now.

08:54.793 --> 08:57.012
One sec, guys, BRB.

08:57.298 --> 08:59.865
You ruin a shot again
and I will put you in ICU.

08:59.867 --> 09:01.033
HEATHER: He's just trying to go

09:01.035 --> 09:02.835
to the bathroom, and
it's right behind you.

09:02.837 --> 09:04.937
No, no, it-it's fine. I
can get out of the shot.

09:04.939 --> 09:07.200
I'll just crawl on the floor.
I'm sure they mop it frequently.

09:07.225 --> 09:08.874
Are you done talking?

09:08.876 --> 09:09.875
Rebecca's friends are waiting

09:09.877 --> 09:11.210
for their daily dose of inspiration.

09:11.212 --> 09:12.344
And they're gonna
think something is wrong

09:12.346 --> 09:14.317
or maybe feel upset, I don't know.

09:14.649 --> 09:16.731
(exhales)

09:17.138 --> 09:22.508
Like I was saying, our little
Becky Girl is going home.

09:22.557 --> 09:24.023
Yay.

09:24.025 --> 09:25.658
You okay?

09:25.937 --> 09:27.780
Need me to wipe anything?

09:27.805 --> 09:30.288
REBECCA: Uh, no, it was weird
last time when you did that.

09:30.313 --> 09:33.566
Yeah, I shouldn't have looked you
right in the eyes. Copy that.

09:33.763 --> 09:35.483
Paula?

09:36.037 --> 09:37.870
I know exactly what's
gonna happen today.

09:37.872 --> 09:39.865
Dr. Shin, he's gonna
prescribe me a bunch of meds,

09:39.890 --> 09:42.074
like doctors always do,
and they're not gonna work,

09:42.076 --> 09:43.576
and I'm gonna end up back here.

09:43.578 --> 09:44.910
Wait, wait, wait.

09:44.912 --> 09:46.545
Let's give the guy a chance.

09:46.547 --> 09:49.267
Remember? Dr. Damn... is good people.

09:49.292 --> 09:51.517
Dr. Damn... it's funny
that you call him that.

09:51.519 --> 09:53.586
These are the moments
when I used to laugh.

09:53.963 --> 09:55.888
So, ha, ha, ha, ha.

09:56.259 --> 09:57.723
Hello, Rebecca.

09:57.725 --> 10:01.160
How we feeling today?
“We,” sorry, that's lame doctor-talk.

10:01.162 --> 10:02.695
How are you feeling today?

10:02.697 --> 10:04.530
Um, I, um, all right.

10:04.532 --> 10:06.966
PAULA: So, you're springing
our girl today.

10:06.968 --> 10:08.968
I can't wait to get
her back home with me.

10:08.970 --> 10:10.035
You two live together?

10:10.037 --> 10:11.804
Oh, no, no, no. No,
I live with my husband

10:11.806 --> 10:13.706
and kids, but you know,
my focus is Rebecca

10:13.708 --> 10:15.608
right now, so I will be

10:15.610 --> 10:18.844
driving her and staying with
her and sleeping in her bed.

10:18.846 --> 10:20.499
- In her bed?
- Yes.

10:20.524 --> 10:22.715
Oh, I'm sorry, have you never
had a best friend before?

10:22.717 --> 10:24.350
Because you should talk
to someone about that.

10:24.352 --> 10:27.519
REBECCA: O-Okay, so, um,
all right, Doc, tell me what to do.

10:27.521 --> 10:29.989
Um, first question, how
many meds am I gonna be on?

10:29.991 --> 10:31.924
Uh, can you give me the daytime
version of whatever it is?

10:31.926 --> 10:34.126
Because all of the other
meds I've been prescribed

10:34.128 --> 10:36.110
have made me numb or drowsy or...

10:36.135 --> 10:39.837
Actually, your treatment protocol
is not centered on medication.

10:39.862 --> 10:42.234
- Wait, what?
- Yeah, how is she supposed

10:42.236 --> 10:43.569
to get better with no medicine?

10:43.571 --> 10:46.472
Oh, there may be some, but
it's not the main focus.

10:46.474 --> 10:50.910
Rebecca, in my opinion, you've
been misdiagnosed over the years.

10:50.912 --> 10:53.875
It's one of the main reasons
you've been struggling.

10:53.900 --> 10:57.101
I think, with the right
diagnosis and treatment,

10:57.585 --> 10:58.884
you can get a lot better.

10:59.336 --> 11:01.587
Wait, so you have a
new diagnosis for me?

11:01.589 --> 11:03.689
So I'm not anxious or OCD

11:03.691 --> 11:05.090
or depressed or any of
the vague combo of things

11:05.092 --> 11:06.258
people have told me I am?

11:06.260 --> 11:08.761
- Oh-oh, my God. What am I?
- Great questions,

11:08.763 --> 11:10.396
but I don't want to
get ahead of treatment.

11:10.398 --> 11:12.423
Okay? We're gonna talk about all that

11:12.448 --> 11:15.267
and the steps towards your recovery
later today at the clinic.

11:15.269 --> 11:17.069
Wow, this is huge.

11:17.071 --> 11:19.405
- I'll see you then, okay?
- Okay.

11:19.407 --> 11:21.064
Bye.

11:21.242 --> 11:24.109
Paula, did you hear what he said?

11:24.111 --> 11:26.879
I have a new diagnosis. A new one.

11:26.881 --> 11:28.147
♪ ♪

11:28.149 --> 11:29.648
He just opened up

11:29.650 --> 11:33.152
a whole new future of
possibilities for me.

11:33.154 --> 11:35.654
A new path for my life.

11:38.659 --> 11:41.894
♪ For almost 30 years, I've
known something was wrong ♪

11:41.896 --> 11:43.762
♪ But Mom said weakness
causes bloating ♪

11:43.764 --> 11:45.631
♪ So I tried to be strong ♪

11:45.633 --> 11:47.199
♪ Fake it till you make it ♪

11:47.201 --> 11:50.882
♪ That's how I got by ♪

11:51.672 --> 11:53.572
♪ And when I tried
to find the reason ♪

11:53.574 --> 11:55.407
♪ For my sadness and terror ♪

11:55.409 --> 11:58.744
♪ All the solutions
were trial and error ♪

11:58.746 --> 12:00.746
♪ Take this pill, say this chant ♪

12:00.748 --> 12:04.650
♪ Move here for this guy ♪

12:04.652 --> 12:08.420
♪ But now, there's
no need for regret ♪

12:08.422 --> 12:10.689
♪ 'Cause I'm about to get ♪

12:10.691 --> 12:14.159
♪ A diagnosis ♪

12:14.161 --> 12:17.429
♪ A diagnosis ♪

12:17.431 --> 12:23.736
♪ Don't tell me, “No,
sister, you don't fit in” ♪

12:24.805 --> 12:28.340
♪ Doc, prescribe me my
tribe, give me my throng ♪

12:28.342 --> 12:31.377
♪ Tell me that this
whole time I've belonged ♪

12:31.379 --> 12:34.213
♪ With those other
people who share ♪

12:34.215 --> 12:38.150
♪ My diagnosis ♪

12:38.152 --> 12:41.286
♪ What could it be?
What could be right? ♪

12:41.288 --> 12:44.790
♪ Schizophrenic or bipolar lite? ♪

12:44.792 --> 12:46.291
♪ I've never heard voices ♪

12:46.293 --> 12:48.727
♪ But maybe it's time to start... ♪

12:48.729 --> 12:50.562
VOICES: You're super cool, Rebecca.

12:50.564 --> 12:51.630
Thanks.

12:51.632 --> 12:52.998
♪ Obsessives with numbers ♪

12:53.000 --> 12:55.134
♪ Hoarders with cats ♪

12:55.136 --> 12:57.970
♪ I could really
rock a tinfoil hat ♪

12:57.972 --> 13:01.407
♪ Perfect they're not,
but at least they know ♪

13:01.409 --> 13:03.609
♪ Who they are ♪

13:03.611 --> 13:04.743
- (gasps)
- _

13:04.745 --> 13:08.013
♪ No more bad pills,
fads or tricks ♪

13:08.015 --> 13:11.850
♪ Who says there isn't an easy fix ♪

13:11.852 --> 13:15.087
♪ With a diagnosis ♪

13:15.089 --> 13:19.291
♪ I'm ready to blow this ♪

13:19.293 --> 13:23.429
♪ Joint, and by joint, I mean
my inner sense of confusion ♪

13:23.431 --> 13:25.597
- VOICES: ♪ You said that confusingly ♪
- Shh.

13:25.599 --> 13:28.801
♪ I'm aware mental
illness is stigmatized ♪

13:28.803 --> 13:32.471
♪ But the stigma is worth
it if I've realized ♪

13:32.473 --> 13:34.706
♪ Who I'm meant to be ♪

13:34.708 --> 13:39.178
♪ Armed with my diagnosis ♪

13:39.180 --> 13:41.013
♪ Oh, the doctors that I've met ♪

13:41.015 --> 13:44.983
♪ Who didn't get me ♪

13:44.985 --> 13:47.286
♪ This one naturopath ♪

13:47.288 --> 13:51.924
♪ Used feathers to pet me ♪

13:51.926 --> 13:54.960
♪ They said anxiety,
insomnia were my affliction ♪

13:54.962 --> 13:58.730
♪ The naturopath said
it was sex addiction ♪

13:58.732 --> 14:02.167
♪ But all those things
I knew I wasn't ♪

14:02.169 --> 14:06.505
♪ Yes, I like penises,
but who doesn't? ♪

14:06.507 --> 14:10.509
♪ So put me in a
bottle, slap a label on ♪

14:10.511 --> 14:13.479
♪ List out the side effects,
then worries begone ♪

14:13.481 --> 14:16.915
♪ 'Cause finally, I'll know this ♪

14:16.917 --> 14:21.453
♪ My diagnosis! ♪

14:21.455 --> 14:24.007
- (exhales)
- Welcome to your therapy, Rebecca.

14:28.679 --> 14:30.398
_

14:30.422 --> 14:31.906
Okay. Diagnosis time. Hit me.

14:31.930 --> 14:34.724
Okay. Now, it's
important to keep in mind

14:34.749 --> 14:37.483
that nobody's diagnosis is
simple or covers everything.

14:37.508 --> 14:39.175
- Yep, yep, yep, yep.
- It's also important

14:39.177 --> 14:41.771
to not look up the diagnosis online

14:41.796 --> 14:43.612
before we have a chance
to get into it, okay?

14:43.614 --> 14:45.233
Got it. I will not look up anything,

14:45.258 --> 14:46.791
if you don't want me
to. I'm a good student.

14:46.793 --> 14:48.960
I will stick to the
required reading, sir.

14:48.962 --> 14:52.563
Rebecca, I am noticing
how energetic you are.

14:52.565 --> 14:55.233
That's not uncommon
after a suicidal event.

14:55.729 --> 14:58.569
Too energetic. Sorry. Sorry, um, sorry.

14:58.571 --> 15:01.606
I'm-I'm calm now, this
is my calm, low voice.

15:01.631 --> 15:03.441
Okay, so,

15:03.443 --> 15:06.277
based on my conversation
with Dr. Akopian

15:06.279 --> 15:08.646
and our meetings at the hospital,

15:08.648 --> 15:12.517
it is my belief that, while
you do have some symptoms

15:12.519 --> 15:15.353
of anxiety, depression, OCD

15:15.355 --> 15:16.687
and possibly PTSD...

15:16.689 --> 15:17.922
Right. But I've heard
all those things before,

15:17.924 --> 15:20.158
- and you said this was a new thing.
- I'm still talking.

15:20.160 --> 15:21.893
- Sorry.
- It is my opinion

15:21.895 --> 15:24.195
that you exhibit many
of the characteristics

15:24.197 --> 15:27.265
of borderline personality disorder.

15:28.139 --> 15:31.084
Wow. O-Okay, um...

15:31.383 --> 15:34.184
First question... what is that?

15:34.374 --> 15:38.037
Well, a person with BPD
is essentially someone

15:38.062 --> 15:41.012
who has difficulty
regulating their emotions.

15:41.014 --> 15:45.416
Someone that lacks the
protective emotional skin

15:45.418 --> 15:47.552
to feel comfortable in the world.

15:47.554 --> 15:49.140
Wow.

15:49.483 --> 15:51.759
Um, just a couple questions, um...

15:51.784 --> 15:53.825
How did I get BPD? Is BPD curable?

15:53.827 --> 15:55.827
How serious is BPD?
Is BPD easy to fix?

15:55.829 --> 15:57.795
Is BPD genetic? Did I get
the BPD from my mother?

15:57.797 --> 15:59.630
I got it from my mother, right?
Again, just, like, rapid fire.

15:59.632 --> 16:01.632
Just, like, answer.
Don't think about it.

16:01.634 --> 16:03.434
Okay, I never fall for “rapid fire.”

16:03.436 --> 16:06.771
Rebecca, I know you have a lot
of questions. I understand.

16:06.773 --> 16:08.840
And we'll talk about
it a lot more, luckily,

16:08.842 --> 16:11.108
in your group therapy, which
is where we're headed right now.

16:11.110 --> 16:13.077
So you're just gonna pull a
Yoda and not tell me anything

16:13.079 --> 16:15.279
I want to know before I'm
ready to know it, yeah?

16:15.281 --> 16:16.424
That's what this is?

16:16.950 --> 16:19.650
Hot-ass doctor, telling me not
to look things up online.

16:19.652 --> 16:21.152
Oh, I'm gonna look things up online,

16:21.154 --> 16:22.787
hot-ass doctor. All right.

16:22.789 --> 16:26.591
“What is borderline
personality disorder?”

16:26.593 --> 16:28.793
(exhales)

16:30.174 --> 16:32.174
_

16:32.199 --> 16:34.199
_

16:34.224 --> 16:35.858
_

16:35.882 --> 16:37.592
_

16:37.617 --> 16:39.617
_

16:39.641 --> 16:41.641
_

16:41.741 --> 16:43.007
Nope.

16:43.009 --> 16:45.343
No. No, no, no. No.

16:45.345 --> 16:46.644
So, guys.

16:46.646 --> 16:47.745
Guys, guys, guys.

16:47.747 --> 16:49.780
Day five, part two.

16:49.782 --> 16:52.116
Rebecca is at the outpatient center

16:52.118 --> 16:53.751
getting wonderful treatment.

16:53.753 --> 16:55.553
And meanwhile, back at the ranch,

16:55.555 --> 16:59.156
we've stocked up on all of
her favorite... comfort carbs.

16:59.158 --> 17:01.459
My girl loves her sugar, salt and dough.

17:01.461 --> 17:03.828
Now, all of you supporters out there,

17:03.830 --> 17:06.063
Rebecca's big #Bunchafriends,

17:06.065 --> 17:08.799
I want you to know that
her heart is strong,

17:08.800 --> 17:10.501
her spirit is bright, and she...

17:10.502 --> 17:11.836
Did you tell all your bots

17:11.838 --> 17:13.871
that we had to take all
the knives out of the house?

17:13.873 --> 17:15.406
Also, maybe ask them if they know

17:15.407 --> 17:18.075
how to jailbreak an
avocado, because I do not.

17:18.077 --> 17:19.175
Heather, we're live.

17:19.178 --> 17:20.444
- Okay.
- (door opens)

17:20.445 --> 17:21.545
Oh, my God, guys, she's here.

17:21.547 --> 17:23.681
Guys, guys, guys, let's see how it went.

17:23.683 --> 17:26.284
(door closes)

17:26.286 --> 17:30.154
- Okay, let's put that away.
- (phone beeps)

17:30.156 --> 17:34.525
REBECCA: So, um, I got the worst
diagnosis ever, basically, um...

17:34.527 --> 17:35.826
Yeah, I really hate it.

17:35.828 --> 17:38.529
It's, uh, called borderline
personality disorder,

17:38.531 --> 17:40.765
and I read two and a
half sentences about it,

17:40.767 --> 17:42.300
and they were the worst sentences ever,

17:42.302 --> 17:44.068
and I don't want to know any more.

17:44.070 --> 17:46.581
(crying): And it's all just awful.

17:46.606 --> 17:48.506
(phone beeps)

17:48.508 --> 17:49.907
(mouthing)

17:49.909 --> 17:51.809
Oh, my God. Stop.

17:52.612 --> 17:56.013
“Wishing you the best

17:56.015 --> 17:59.517
“after your suicide attempt.

17:59.519 --> 18:03.287
“Yours, Nathaniel J. Plimpton III,

18:03.289 --> 18:05.022
Esquire.”

18:07.961 --> 18:09.446
Yeah.

18:17.570 --> 18:19.603
(exhales)

18:19.605 --> 18:21.806
(panting)

18:29.415 --> 18:31.382
- (groans)
- What's up, boss?

18:31.384 --> 18:32.984
Uh, nothing.

18:32.986 --> 18:36.732
Uh, just had a little
weird déjà vu moment.

18:37.090 --> 18:38.589
So glad you called me in...

18:38.591 --> 18:41.092
- I did no such thing.
- ... because we are planning

18:41.094 --> 18:43.160
to visit Rebecca at home this weekend.

18:43.162 --> 18:46.263
I'm kind of nervous,
'cause I'm terrible with death.

18:46.265 --> 18:47.765
When I was a kid, my dog died.

18:47.767 --> 18:52.343
- I was the one who found him,
- all, like, splayed out,

18:52.952 --> 18:55.906
eyes rolled into the back of his head,

18:55.908 --> 18:57.475
his tongue hanging out.

18:57.477 --> 18:58.809
It's, like, burned into my brain...

18:58.811 --> 18:59.944
Stop it!

18:59.946 --> 19:01.679
Oh.

19:01.681 --> 19:03.014
I'm sorry.

19:03.016 --> 19:04.682
Don't worry about me.

19:04.684 --> 19:07.518
I'm a cat guy now.
I have a cat named Andromeda...

19:07.520 --> 19:09.053
I got to go.

19:09.055 --> 19:10.287
Are... you...

19:10.289 --> 19:11.555
Just get out of my office.

19:11.557 --> 19:13.057
Okay, well.

19:14.228 --> 19:17.628
So you didn't go to group
therapy, you just blew it off?

19:17.630 --> 19:18.863
No, I didn't go.

19:18.865 --> 19:20.587
I was too upset.

19:20.967 --> 19:24.635
I mean, I don't have an illness,
I have a personality disorder.

19:24.892 --> 19:28.305
It's not something I
have, it's something I am.

19:28.307 --> 19:30.908
This is what I've feared
my whole life. I'm broken.

19:30.910 --> 19:34.311
Honey, what did I say to
you over and over in the car?

19:34.313 --> 19:35.479
You are not broken.

19:35.481 --> 19:36.714
You're wonderful.

19:36.716 --> 19:37.882
VALENCIA: She's right.

19:37.884 --> 19:40.251
You are an inspiration
to hundreds of people.

19:40.253 --> 19:42.720
There is a Facebook group in Venezuela

19:42.722 --> 19:44.755
that's completely devoted to you.

19:44.757 --> 19:47.324
It's called El Buncho Valiente.

19:47.326 --> 19:49.393
Oh, my God, seriously, stop.

19:49.395 --> 19:52.263
Okay, listen, Rebecca, if you
hate this diagnosis so much,

19:52.265 --> 19:55.132
then, let's get a second opinion.

19:55.398 --> 19:57.268
Second opinions are very common.

19:57.270 --> 19:59.070
And, you know, this new doctor,

19:59.072 --> 20:00.805
he just met you.

20:00.807 --> 20:02.406
He doesn't know you yet.

20:02.408 --> 20:04.275
And who says we just have to sit here

20:04.277 --> 20:07.311
and accept his diagnosis
with a capital “D”?

20:07.313 --> 20:09.547
We don't have to just take his “D.”

20:09.549 --> 20:11.015
Who says his “D" is so great?

20:11.017 --> 20:12.550
No, you're right. He
should get to know me better

20:12.552 --> 20:14.318
before he shoves his
“D” down my throat.

20:14.320 --> 20:15.553
Yeah. What we should do,

20:15.555 --> 20:17.254
is get another “D.”

20:17.256 --> 20:19.323
And then we'll have two Ds.

20:19.325 --> 20:20.758
You know, one here, and one there,

20:20.760 --> 20:22.059
and we'll just...

20:22.061 --> 20:25.929
- figure out which “D” you like better.
- Okay, let's calm down.

20:25.954 --> 20:29.233
Rebecca, we can ask Dr. Akopian.

20:29.235 --> 20:32.236
Oh, my God, Paula, you're totally right.

20:32.238 --> 20:33.871
I mean, she knows me
way better than Dr. Shin,

20:33.873 --> 20:36.807
and she never said anything
about a personality disorder.

20:36.809 --> 20:38.509
I mean, she likes me a lot.

20:38.511 --> 20:41.779
I-I thought Dr. Akopian
consulted with Dr. Damn

20:41.781 --> 20:43.581
on your diagnosis?

20:43.583 --> 20:45.850
She may have, but... no.

20:45.852 --> 20:48.152
I-If she knew how much
I hated this diagnosis,

20:48.154 --> 20:50.254
and how upset it was
making me, she'd be pissed.

20:50.256 --> 20:52.223
I mean, Dr. Akopian only
wants me to be happy,

20:52.225 --> 20:54.204
and this is not what happy feels like.

20:54.229 --> 20:56.594
All right. Let's go. I'll drive.

20:56.596 --> 20:58.462
Okay.

20:58.464 --> 21:00.564
I do recommend an appointment.

21:00.566 --> 21:02.867
Maybe don't crawl
through her doggie door.

21:02.869 --> 21:07.037
Hmm. How do I spin this
for the worldwide audience?

21:07.039 --> 21:08.305
- (door closes)
- (phone beeps)

21:08.307 --> 21:09.440
Oh...

21:09.442 --> 21:11.642
(piano playing softly)

21:12.378 --> 21:14.245
- (knocking on door)
- (door opens)

21:14.247 --> 21:15.579
Father. Mother.

21:15.581 --> 21:17.248
Nathaniel, martini time
cannot be interrupted.

21:17.250 --> 21:18.649
The timing is crucial.

21:18.651 --> 21:19.950
That skin of ice on the top,

21:19.952 --> 21:21.352
it melts in seconds.
Melts. I know, I know.

21:21.354 --> 21:23.187
Oh, it's okay, darling.
He came all this way.

21:23.189 --> 21:24.388
What is it, Nathaniel?

21:24.390 --> 21:25.744
W-Would you like a martini?

21:25.769 --> 21:29.426
- No, no. I need answers.
- I don't like your tone.

21:29.744 --> 21:31.061
Mom.

21:31.455 --> 21:33.898
When I was ten, did you
try to kill yourself?

21:34.507 --> 21:36.340
Not now, Bernice!

21:37.547 --> 21:38.880
Did you?

21:45.643 --> 21:47.677
NATHANIEL: I have this... memory.

21:47.679 --> 21:50.012
I was ten years old, and I
heard something fall over.

21:50.014 --> 21:52.315
And I went to your room, and I saw you,

21:52.317 --> 21:55.528
Mom, passed out on the floor.
And your eyes

21:55.553 --> 21:58.321
were rolling back in your head.
And I tried to wake you up...

21:58.323 --> 21:59.422
Nathaniel, enough.

21:59.424 --> 22:00.823
And Dad told me to go
to my room, and I did.

22:00.825 --> 22:03.359
And then the next thing
I know, you were gone

22:03.361 --> 22:05.094
for, like, a month. And everyone said,

22:05.096 --> 22:06.763
“Don't talk about it.
Don't ask questions.”

22:06.765 --> 22:08.097
So I didn't.

22:08.787 --> 22:10.733
But now I really need
to know what happened.

22:10.735 --> 22:12.268
You know what happened.

22:12.270 --> 22:14.470
Your mother had the
flu and got dehydrated,

22:14.472 --> 22:16.229
so she went sailing for a month

22:16.254 --> 22:19.041
- with your Aunt Sissy in Rhode Island.
- That's right.

22:19.043 --> 22:21.377
I brought you back that
anchor key chain, remember?

22:21.379 --> 22:23.731
It wasn't the flu. Come on.

22:23.756 --> 22:25.989
There were sleeping
pills. There was a bottle

22:26.014 --> 22:28.418
of pills on your nightstand,
and you wouldn't wake up.

22:28.420 --> 22:30.653
We told you what happened.
This conversation is over.

22:30.655 --> 22:32.287
It's not over.

22:33.224 --> 22:35.992
Look, I need to know the truth.

22:35.994 --> 22:37.660
My friend just tried to kill herself,

22:37.662 --> 22:39.228
and I can't reach out to her at all,

22:39.230 --> 22:41.197
because every time I think about her,

22:41.199 --> 22:43.900
I picture this... lifeless body.

22:43.925 --> 22:45.752
And it makes me think of you that night.

22:45.777 --> 22:48.908
And I get panicked and I can't breathe.

22:48.933 --> 22:50.500
And I don't know what that is.

22:50.502 --> 22:53.136
And, I'm sorry, also, who
goes sailing for a month

22:53.138 --> 22:54.804
when they have the
flu? That's not a thing.

22:54.806 --> 22:56.105
That's a terrible lie.

22:56.107 --> 22:59.842
- Please tell me the truth.
- Nathaniel, stop this now.

22:59.844 --> 23:01.778
This isn't how we raised you.

23:02.958 --> 23:04.539
Mom?

23:07.578 --> 23:08.951
Please.

23:09.484 --> 23:12.588
Oh, Nathaniel, I hate
to see you so upset.

23:12.804 --> 23:16.659
But it's-it's just so
unpleasant to dredge up the past.

23:16.661 --> 23:18.428
(clears throat) Now,

23:18.430 --> 23:20.096
why don't you join us for dinner.

23:20.098 --> 23:21.431
We're having lamb tonight.

23:21.433 --> 23:23.499
And-and then you can
come out and see my roses.

23:23.501 --> 23:24.467
They're looking

23:24.469 --> 23:25.501
so healthy...

23:25.503 --> 23:26.869
Will you please just answer me?!

23:30.108 --> 23:31.607
(sighs)

23:31.609 --> 23:34.944
(exhales) I think I'd
better go lie down.

23:34.946 --> 23:37.246
I suddenly have a terrible headache.

23:38.068 --> 23:39.958
Mom, I'm sorry. I...

23:42.716 --> 23:43.989
You upset her.

23:44.716 --> 23:45.822
Something's happened to you

23:45.824 --> 23:48.024
since you started working
in that new office.

23:48.026 --> 23:49.759
You're getting peppery,

23:49.761 --> 23:51.894
and I don't use that word lightly.

23:51.896 --> 23:55.062
Now, congratulations,
you've ruined our evening.

23:55.087 --> 23:57.366
And we were having lamb.

23:57.368 --> 23:58.952
Get out of my house.

24:02.273 --> 24:05.708
VALENCIA: So, guys, I want to
send a special thank you

24:05.710 --> 24:07.643
to Shimmer Glimmer
Cosmetics for sending over

24:07.645 --> 24:10.747
those amazing and gorgeous
lip glosses to Rebecca.

24:10.749 --> 24:14.650
I'm wearing one right now,
and she is going to love them.

24:14.652 --> 24:15.952
There's nothing wrong
with a little pampering

24:15.954 --> 24:17.820
in a tough time... Just
plain ol' self-care.

24:17.822 --> 24:19.622
And, remember, if you
don't like the shade,

24:19.624 --> 24:21.157
Shimmer Glimmer will
send you a different one

24:21.159 --> 24:22.658
- for free... Wait. Okay.
- No, that's enough. I've had it.

24:22.660 --> 24:25.084
- Wait, no! (grunts)
- I've had it. I'm going to murder you.

24:25.109 --> 24:27.196
What is wrong with you?

24:27.198 --> 24:30.299
You're using your friend's
crisis to get swag?

24:30.770 --> 24:33.669
I mean, not to judge, V, like, at all,

24:33.671 --> 24:36.639
but what you're doing is
pathetic and vain and stupid

24:36.641 --> 24:39.245
and cringey and trendy
and selfish and basic.

24:39.270 --> 24:41.711
(gasps) Oh, my God. Wait, hold up.

24:41.713 --> 24:43.346
You think this is about me?

24:43.348 --> 24:45.948
- Yes.
- Are you blind?

24:45.950 --> 24:49.652
This has way transcended any one person.

24:49.654 --> 24:52.155
Rebecca's story and her courage

24:52.157 --> 24:54.257
and my courage sharing her courage

24:54.259 --> 24:56.359
is inspiring an entire movement.

24:56.600 --> 24:58.427
And that's what people want to feel...

24:58.429 --> 25:00.763
Inspired, not sad.

25:00.765 --> 25:02.365
And that is what I give them...

25:02.367 --> 25:04.233
Hope and joy

25:04.235 --> 25:06.469
and, yes, makeup tips and gorgeous hair.

25:06.471 --> 25:07.804
Oh, my God, you're so full of it.

25:07.806 --> 25:09.972
You're, like, so full of crap.

25:09.974 --> 25:11.741
No, I'm not.

25:11.743 --> 25:13.676
I'm full of something else.

