We don't have one. It's a call center.

26:47.405 --> 26:49.305
Yeah, that's not a movement.

26:49.307 --> 26:52.208
♪ Mine is a movement ♪

26:52.210 --> 26:56.178
♪ A big ol' stinky movement, oh ♪

26:56.180 --> 26:59.115
♪ It's gonna be a beauty,
'cause it's my duty ♪

26:59.117 --> 27:01.951
♪ To spread it all over the world ♪

27:01.953 --> 27:03.386
♪ I'm gonna spread it ♪

27:03.388 --> 27:08.190
♪ All over the world. ♪

27:08.947 --> 27:11.594
It sounds like you're
just talking about poop.

27:11.596 --> 27:12.528
What? No.

27:12.530 --> 27:14.384
I rarely poop. It's been a month.

27:14.866 --> 27:16.699
♪ ♪

27:22.250 --> 27:24.968
So, I'm glad to see you here again.

27:24.993 --> 27:27.793
How has everything been
going? How are you feeling?

27:27.795 --> 27:30.234
Uh, not great. Still have
the same problem.

27:30.698 --> 27:34.233
I'm so happy, and I feel
so good all the time.

27:34.235 --> 27:36.029
And that's hard, because

27:36.068 --> 27:37.968
I know not everyone feels that way.

27:37.970 --> 27:40.904
- And that makes me sad.
- I hear you.

27:40.906 --> 27:42.305
And that's wonderful.

27:42.307 --> 27:44.975
But maybe we could circle back
to what you told me last week.

27:44.977 --> 27:46.943
About your mother shooting
your father in cold blood

27:46.945 --> 27:48.244
in front of you on your birthday.

27:48.246 --> 27:49.679
Oh, I've moved beyond that.

27:49.681 --> 27:50.647
(chuckles)

27:50.649 --> 27:52.816
Dr. Akopian, we need to talk to you.

27:52.818 --> 27:55.485
Excuse me. You can't
just burst into my office.

27:55.487 --> 27:56.886
It's okay. It's fine.

27:56.888 --> 27:58.462
Rebecca tried to kill herself.

27:58.487 --> 28:01.191
She needs this more than
I do. Really, I'm good.

28:01.193 --> 28:02.726
- Like I said.
- PAULA: See?

28:02.728 --> 28:05.095
- Kevin is fine with it.
- Go get 'em, champ.

28:05.097 --> 28:08.131
Me and all the Bunchafriends,
we're cheering you on.

28:08.133 --> 28:09.831
No! Kevin!

28:11.169 --> 28:13.136
(sobbing): Why, Mommy, why?!

28:13.138 --> 28:15.773
Rebecca, this is highly inappropriate.

28:15.798 --> 28:18.541
I'm so sorry. I know, I
know. But it's an emergency.

28:18.543 --> 28:20.510
- I think I've been misdiagnosed.
- Yeah.

28:20.512 --> 28:23.079
They told her she had some
stupid personality thing.

28:23.081 --> 28:25.348
REBECCA: Okay, and I know that
Dr. Shin consulted with you,

28:25.350 --> 28:27.517
but I think he tricked you
into giving me that diagnosis

28:27.519 --> 28:29.419
by mansplaining you into it.

28:29.421 --> 28:32.288
Rebecca, did you talk to Dr. Shin?

28:32.290 --> 28:35.125
- Did you go to your group therapy?
- No, I did not.

28:35.127 --> 28:37.127
Because I don't want to
hear any more about it.

28:37.129 --> 28:39.095
I know it's wrong. I know
in my heart it's wrong.

28:39.097 --> 28:40.897
So just give me a new thing,
okay? Give me the thing I know

28:40.899 --> 28:43.166
you want to give me. Right?
'Cause it's a better thing.

28:44.903 --> 28:45.802
One, two, three, go.

28:45.804 --> 28:47.404
JOSH: So, um,

28:47.406 --> 28:48.571
okay, I'm ready.

28:48.573 --> 28:50.707
Give it to me straight.

28:50.709 --> 28:52.609
What is Rebecca saying about me?

28:52.611 --> 28:54.044
I've been there basically every day.

28:54.046 --> 28:55.645
Haven't heard your name once.

28:55.647 --> 28:56.813
You don't have to shield me.

28:56.815 --> 28:58.248
I can take it.

28:58.506 --> 29:02.018
I am responsible for someone
almost taking their life.

29:02.194 --> 29:04.554
Look, from what I picked
up in the hospital...

29:04.556 --> 29:06.189
And I'm in the inner circle;

29:06.191 --> 29:07.724
I provide snacks, advice,

29:07.726 --> 29:10.160
and an outlet for
Valencia's aggression...

29:10.162 --> 29:12.095
Being suicidal has nothing to do

29:12.097 --> 29:14.130
with any one life event or person.

29:14.132 --> 29:17.000
It's more of a general
mental illness thing.

29:17.002 --> 29:19.335
Um, yeah. Well, Rebecca
has been obsessed with me

29:19.337 --> 29:21.738
since she was 16. I ruined her.

29:21.740 --> 29:24.974
Suicide is a cardinal sin,
and I almost sin-assisted.

29:24.976 --> 29:26.309
No, this is on me, man.

29:26.311 --> 29:27.977
I-I've got to do something,

29:27.979 --> 29:29.946
see Rebecca, make things right.

29:29.948 --> 29:30.947
(sighs)

29:30.949 --> 29:32.315
Or you don't.

29:32.317 --> 29:33.349
Or I do.

29:33.351 --> 29:34.350
Or you really don't.

29:34.352 --> 29:35.218
I do, though.

29:35.220 --> 29:36.586
I don't think you really do.

29:36.588 --> 29:39.022
Except that I do, I think.

29:39.024 --> 29:40.056
I don't think so.

29:40.058 --> 29:41.591
AKOPIAN: Rebecca, it sounds

29:41.593 --> 29:44.828
like you don't have accurate
information about borderline.

29:44.830 --> 29:47.997
Dr. Shin asked you not
to look it up online,

29:47.999 --> 29:50.700
- but I'm suspecting that you did.
- So what?

29:50.702 --> 29:52.635
Yeah, I did. So what? All right.

29:52.637 --> 29:55.139
Why don't we take a sec
and look at the checklist,

29:55.164 --> 29:56.773
see if anything resonates.

29:56.775 --> 29:58.475
- What checklist?
- To determine

29:58.477 --> 30:00.610
whether or not a person has BPD.

30:02.124 --> 30:05.715
A checklist sounds like
homework. You like homework.

30:05.717 --> 30:07.984
Wait, why don't we just hear
it and then see what we think?

30:07.986 --> 30:10.285
I mean, I am right here.
I am right next to you.

30:10.310 --> 30:12.522
Yes, you are.

30:12.524 --> 30:14.724
Which is a whole nother
thing we should talk about.

30:14.726 --> 30:16.126
- I don't... I don't...
- All right,

30:16.128 --> 30:18.461
in order to receive a diagnosis for BPD,

30:18.463 --> 30:20.530
a person has to have at least five

30:20.532 --> 30:22.565
of the following nine tendencies.

30:22.567 --> 30:24.334
Just keep an open mind.

30:24.336 --> 30:27.337
Okay? Okay, the first one is

30:27.339 --> 30:29.906
severe mood swings.

30:29.908 --> 30:31.474
♪ ♪

30:31.476 --> 30:33.376
(chuckles) Well, we'll see about that.

30:33.378 --> 30:34.544
(both laugh)

30:34.546 --> 30:36.913
We'll see about that.

30:37.829 --> 30:40.483
Profound fear of abandonment.

30:40.875 --> 30:43.609
Josh. Hey, no, Josh!

30:44.343 --> 30:47.223
Instability in relationships.

30:47.225 --> 30:50.226
It's like you think I'm your
daughter or something, but I'm not.

30:51.563 --> 30:53.554
Unstable sense of identity.

30:53.579 --> 30:56.266
I don't know who I am if
you're not in my life anymore.

30:57.572 --> 31:00.807
Paranoia or dissociative episodes.

31:01.106 --> 31:03.106
What? Robert.

31:03.108 --> 31:04.108
No!

31:05.810 --> 31:08.011
Excessive and frequent anger.

31:08.013 --> 31:09.646
Stop running, you coward!

31:10.982 --> 31:13.116
Feelings of emptiness.

31:13.118 --> 31:16.019
My womb is empty, like my life.

31:17.522 --> 31:18.955
Impulsive behavior.

31:18.957 --> 31:20.657
(moaning)

31:24.444 --> 31:25.895
And, finally,

31:25.897 --> 31:30.033
recurring suicide threats or attempts.

31:31.818 --> 31:33.816
Oh, my God.

31:34.773 --> 31:35.939
I know.

31:35.941 --> 31:37.540
So not you, right?

31:37.542 --> 31:38.841
(chuckles)

31:38.843 --> 31:40.410
Paula,

31:40.511 --> 31:42.344
all those things were me.

31:43.051 --> 31:45.574
I don't have five... I have nine.

31:46.218 --> 31:48.618
(sighs)

31:55.062 --> 31:57.629
(crickets chirping)

31:58.897 --> 32:01.635
Hey. How'd it go?
Did you get a new diagnosis?

32:01.660 --> 32:03.433
No. Uh, same one.

32:03.435 --> 32:05.826
But it's right.

32:06.357 --> 32:09.739
Yeah, the verdict's in.
I am officially, medically,

32:09.741 --> 32:12.990
certifiably “crazy.”

32:13.378 --> 32:15.445
Well, no one said anything about crazy.

32:15.447 --> 32:19.048
Um, so, look, I-I
appreciate everyone's support.

32:19.050 --> 32:20.650
And I love you guys. I really do. But...

32:20.652 --> 32:23.762
I'm very tired, so...
I'm just gonna go to bed.

32:25.614 --> 32:26.926
Alone.

32:36.925 --> 32:39.392
I'm sure she just needs to rest.

32:39.504 --> 32:41.271
(door lock clicks)

32:51.755 --> 32:53.942
Good morning, Mother.
Nathaniel, you're back.

32:54.255 --> 32:55.988
I waited for Dad to leave.

32:56.575 --> 32:58.153
Mom, I came back

32:58.155 --> 32:59.487
because I wanted to apologize

32:59.489 --> 33:01.122
for how I acted last night.

33:01.124 --> 33:02.691
Oh, no, that's okay.

33:02.693 --> 33:04.459
I know you don't like
to rehash the past,

33:04.461 --> 33:06.040
and I respect that.

33:07.181 --> 33:10.081
I'm not trying to make
you feel bad, really.

33:10.986 --> 33:14.939
I know we don't say this stuff
in our house, but...

33:19.684 --> 33:21.828
I love you, Mom.

33:22.245 --> 33:25.608
And I want you to know
that if you ever need me,

33:25.918 --> 33:27.651
I'm here.

33:29.578 --> 33:31.077
And you're right...

33:31.298 --> 33:33.264
These roses, they really are beautiful.

33:36.656 --> 33:38.210
Nathaniel, wait.

33:41.161 --> 33:44.869
When you were ten, I was
going through a hard time.

33:46.576 --> 33:49.251
I made a mistake with my sleeping pills.

33:50.580 --> 33:52.036
Then I went away for a while

33:52.038 --> 33:55.908
to a place where I learned
to sleep without pills.

33:57.877 --> 34:02.298
There was some sailing there. Not much.

34:03.793 --> 34:05.705
Anyway, you're right.

34:06.142 --> 34:07.685
I should have told you.

34:09.275 --> 34:10.420
Wow.

34:14.726 --> 34:16.527
Did we just have a talk?

34:17.469 --> 34:20.031
- I think we did.
- (both laughing)

34:20.033 --> 34:23.034
- (gasps) Don't tell your father.
- Oh, no, I won't.

34:23.036 --> 34:25.726
Do you want to take some of
these roses to your friend?

34:26.302 --> 34:28.168
I think she'd like them.

34:35.215 --> 34:36.813
What are you guys doing?

34:36.815 --> 34:39.150
- Oh...
- (groans)

34:39.152 --> 34:41.052
Um, just having a sleepover.

34:41.331 --> 34:44.722
Yeah, the floor's so
cozy, I slept great.

34:44.724 --> 34:46.690
All right, guys,
sorry, I got to pee, so,

34:46.693 --> 34:49.560
- I've just got to...
- Oh.

34:49.562 --> 34:52.429
- All right, just watch your step.
- O-Okay.

34:54.850 --> 34:57.001
I can go to the bathroom by myself.

34:57.475 --> 34:59.737
- Yeah, I mean, sure.
- Totally.

34:59.739 --> 35:00.771
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

35:00.773 --> 35:02.473
Yeah.

35:05.535 --> 35:07.568
Okay, we can't do this.

35:08.047 --> 35:09.547
She's gonna sleep, she's
gonna go to the bathroom,

35:09.549 --> 35:11.449
she's gonna cut bagels...
We have to get used to it.

35:11.451 --> 35:13.751
(gasps) Oh, my God, I just remembered.

35:13.753 --> 35:15.353
I left toenail clippers in there.

35:15.355 --> 35:17.455
You clip your nails at my house?

35:17.457 --> 35:18.990
My toenails grow really fast,

35:18.992 --> 35:20.291
and they're super-thick
so I carry these

35:20.293 --> 35:21.759
heavy-duty nail clippers on me.

35:21.761 --> 35:23.928
Okay, okay, let's just, like, calm down.

35:23.930 --> 35:25.463
She's not, like, gonna kill herself

35:25.465 --> 35:28.432
- with your nasty, oversized clippers.
- All right.

35:28.434 --> 35:29.634
(sighs) Let's calm down.

35:29.636 --> 35:31.369
And I'm just, I'm knocking on the door

35:31.371 --> 35:33.703
and see if she's okay, that's all.

35:35.441 --> 35:36.578
Rebecca?

35:41.381 --> 35:42.980
Becca?

35:42.982 --> 35:45.650
(jiggling locked doorknob, knocking)

35:45.652 --> 35:47.251
Becky?

35:47.253 --> 35:51.255
Okay, she's not answering.

35:51.257 --> 35:54.592
- (knocking on door)
- (ear-buds): ♪ Yes, no on the crazy ♪

35:54.594 --> 35:57.461
♪ We hope this helps. ♪

35:57.735 --> 35:59.263
What?

35:59.265 --> 36:01.265
She never locks the bathroom door.

36:01.267 --> 36:02.934
Heather's right. Let's not panic.

36:02.936 --> 36:04.569
Okay, all right. (gasps)

36:04.571 --> 36:06.037
What are you doing?

36:06.039 --> 36:08.406
This is my intruder ax. I
can't just stand out here.

36:08.408 --> 36:10.007
I thought you put all
the sharp things away.

36:10.009 --> 36:11.642
I live in a famous murder house.

36:11.644 --> 36:13.077
You think I don't have an ax?

36:13.079 --> 36:14.212
Do it! Do it!

36:14.214 --> 36:16.314
- Just chop it down.
- Just chop it...

36:16.316 --> 36:19.283
(screaming)

36:20.587 --> 36:22.253
Hey, girl.

36:22.255 --> 36:24.046
How was your pee?

36:30.230 --> 36:32.683
What is going on?

36:32.708 --> 36:35.542
Okay, so we may have
been a touch worried.

36:35.544 --> 36:37.911
You didn't answer the
door when we knocked.

36:37.913 --> 36:39.146
I had ear-buds in.

36:39.488 --> 36:41.615
- Oh, ear-buds.
- Ear-buds, right.

36:41.617 --> 36:43.934
In your ears, so you couldn't...

36:43.959 --> 36:45.168
Makes total sense.

36:45.587 --> 36:47.654
I'm sorry to worry you
guys. Look, I was in there

36:47.656 --> 36:49.156
doing this thing that I sometimes do

36:49.158 --> 36:50.857
to make sense of things, I was...

36:50.859 --> 36:54.127
listening to music and
watching music videos and, yeah.

36:54.129 --> 36:56.463
Oh, yeah, cool, because we just thought

36:56.465 --> 37:00.300
- you were killing yourself.
- (sobbing)

37:01.196 --> 37:04.137
We thought you were dead.

37:04.139 --> 37:06.439
We thought we were gonna open the door,

37:06.441 --> 37:07.874
and you'd be all kinds of dead.

37:07.876 --> 37:10.377
I'm so afraid you're gonna die, Rebecca.

37:10.379 --> 37:13.046
I'm so scared. (sniffs)

37:13.048 --> 37:16.383
I have never had a
friend like you before.

37:16.706 --> 37:20.253
I... almost lost you.

37:20.255 --> 37:23.890
And I have been telling all
these people... to have hope,

37:23.892 --> 37:26.993
when, really, I am so sad and so scared,

37:26.995 --> 37:30.297
and I have to poop so, so bad.

37:30.299 --> 37:32.732
- Oh, honey.
- Oh.

37:33.041 --> 37:35.612
(Valencia sobs)

37:36.556 --> 37:38.438
Rebecca, please.

37:39.025 --> 37:42.042
Promise me you'll never do it again.

37:42.652 --> 37:45.619
I... I would lo... I would
love to promise you that.

37:46.715 --> 37:48.673
I'd love to promise you all that.

37:49.797 --> 37:51.530
But I can't.

37:53.322 --> 37:54.971
Look...

37:55.666 --> 37:57.691
The way I felt on that plane, I don't,

37:57.693 --> 37:59.471
I don't ever want to
feel like that again.

38:00.362 --> 38:04.174
And now that I know... what I have,

38:05.502 --> 38:07.834
I hope I can get the help that I need,

38:07.836 --> 38:09.936
but... the truth is,

38:09.938 --> 38:12.533
I don't know what the future holds.

38:13.619 --> 38:16.945
So I just can't promise
anything to anyone, even myself.

38:18.601 --> 38:22.226
You know, for someone who's “crazy,”

38:22.463 --> 38:24.992
you sound pretty sane.

38:26.911 --> 38:28.672
Thank you, Heather.

38:31.426 --> 38:34.027
And I'm so sorry that
I put you through this.

38:34.029 --> 38:35.295
Really.

38:35.297 --> 38:37.063
- Where is she?
- (gasps)

38:37.065 --> 38:39.499
Where's my girl? Oh, I
came as soon as I heard.

38:39.501 --> 38:42.435
She's fine, but what happened to you?

38:42.437 --> 38:45.305
WiJo and I were in a
yurt, totally off the grid,

38:45.307 --> 38:47.274
and for one second, I got cell service,

38:47.276 --> 38:48.842
and all these messages came through,

38:48.844 --> 38:51.011
and I saw what was happening with you,

38:51.013 --> 38:53.813
so I borrowed this tank top from
WiJo because it was so hot out,

38:53.815 --> 38:55.548
and then I hopped in my
car, but it wouldn't start

38:55.550 --> 38:57.050
because the battery died,

38:57.052 --> 38:58.518
so I found a guy in
one of the other yurts,

38:58.520 --> 39:01.154
and I borrowed his car,
but it was a convertible.

39:01.156 --> 39:04.024
And there was so much traffic
coming from the desert.

39:04.026 --> 39:06.927
So I just drove three hours in the sun.

39:06.929 --> 39:08.728
And I didn't stop for sunscreen.

39:08.730 --> 39:11.331
I had a hat but it fell
off after five minutes.

39:11.434 --> 39:14.200
I knew I was burning, but
I had to come see my girl.

39:14.202 --> 39:15.762
- Who needs skin?
- Oh.

39:15.787 --> 39:18.905
- Oh. No, no, no. I'm sorry.
- Sorry, sorry. Sorry, sorry, sorry.

39:18.907 --> 39:21.341
- You've been through so much.
- No, Darryl,

39:21.343 --> 39:22.976
I want to apologize...

39:22.978 --> 39:24.411
for all the horrible
things I said to you

39:24.413 --> 39:25.679
before I left for New York.

39:25.681 --> 39:28.315
It w... they were,
they were all terrible.

39:28.317 --> 39:29.683
I want to apologize to all of you guys.

39:29.685 --> 39:31.618
You know I didn't
mean any of that stuff.

39:31.620 --> 39:34.387
I know that. We know that.

39:34.389 --> 39:36.289
- Of course we do.
- Absolutely. No question.

39:36.291 --> 39:38.291
(overlapping chatter)

39:38.293 --> 39:41.661
DARRYL: I swear to God, when I
get my hands on that Josh Chan...

39:41.663 --> 39:43.296
When I get my hands on that jerk,

39:43.298 --> 39:44.931
I'm gonna give him a piece of my mind.

39:44.933 --> 39:46.199
Because you know what?

39:46.201 --> 39:48.223
I could murder Josh right now.

39:48.248 --> 39:49.803
I do have an ax.

39:49.805 --> 39:52.105
Good. This is all his fault.

39:52.107 --> 39:53.606
REBECCA: Darryl, calm down.

39:53.608 --> 39:55.275
This is not Josh's fault.

39:56.711 --> 40:00.580
I mean, it feels weird
to even say Josh's name.

40:01.000 --> 40:03.414
I-I haven't thought about him in days.

40:03.919 --> 40:06.016
Truly. I mean, it-it's almost like...

40:06.822 --> 40:08.727
Josh is irrelevant.

40:09.324 --> 40:11.398
It's not even about Josh.

40:13.546 --> 40:15.453
Maybe it never was.

40:17.961 --> 40:20.233
Oh, Darryl, honey,
let's-let's get you in...

40:20.664 --> 40:22.135
I don't know, some sort of ice bath.

40:22.137 --> 40:23.670
DARRYL: What does it
mean when it blisters?

40:23.672 --> 40:24.971
REBECCA: Oh. Okay.

40:24.973 --> 40:26.973
No one touch him. No one touch him.

40:28.577 --> 40:30.143
So I'm here.

40:30.145 --> 40:32.645
And I'm ready to face it all.

40:32.647 --> 40:34.814
And I'm ready to start
group therapy, too.

40:34.816 --> 40:36.216
I think you'll like it.

40:36.218 --> 40:38.585
Everyone is really nice and supportive.

40:38.587 --> 40:40.253
But, like, nuts, right?

40:40.255 --> 40:42.455
(laughs) Let's go.

40:42.457 --> 40:44.024
But you didn't answer me.

40:44.026 --> 40:45.831
Are they, are they all terrible?

40:49.765 --> 40:51.865
(sighs)

40:53.828 --> 40:55.568
You were not supposed to see me.

40:55.570 --> 40:57.804
I didn't know you delivered stuff.

40:57.806 --> 40:59.172
This your side hustle?

40:59.174 --> 41:00.573
(chuckles)

41:00.575 --> 41:01.775
Oh.

41:01.800 --> 41:04.546
Oh, these are beautiful.

41:10.519 --> 41:12.085
Wow, this is really sweet.

41:12.087 --> 41:13.586
Well, I mean it.

